Dialogue: 5,0:03:04.03,0:03:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry! Did I keep you?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:07.53,0:03:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with you, Houtarou?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:08.99,0:03:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 5,0:03:10.24,0:03:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you no shame?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:12.29,0:03:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, did you do your research?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:15.30,0:03:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:16.90,0:03:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Find anything interesting?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:18.34,0:03:19.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sort of.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:19.69,0:03:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to hearing your hypothesis.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:23.00,0:03:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap. I forgot to write one.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:27.35,0:03:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's go.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:29.52,0:03:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{gounou}The Chitanda farmer family has one of the best mansions in Kamiyama!
Dialogue: 5,0:03:50.87,0:03:52.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be having fun.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:52.99,0:03:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duh! Cycling is fun!
Dialogue: 5,0:03:55.44,0:03:58.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm using my legs to divide the wind! This feeling{\fscx200}-
Dialogue: 5,0:03:58.75,0:04:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I mean with your high school life in general.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:03.49,0:04:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. The whole "rosy" thing.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:08.31,0:04:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I try to keep a rosy lifestyle wherever I go.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:12.44,0:04:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean shocking pink?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:15.91,0:04:17.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good one.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:17.02,0:04:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By that logic, you're gray.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:19.09,0:04:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been through this already.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:21.27,0:04:22.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:22.40,0:04:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't trying to mock you.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:26.90,0:04:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I have a shocking pink lifestyle.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:29.66,0:04:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one can change that about me.{No one can paint me into a rose color.}
Dialogue: 5,0:04:33.00,0:04:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let 'em.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:34.89,0:04:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you painted all over? {maybe a liberal tl?}
Dialogue: 5,0:04:36.54,0:04:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:37.75,0:04:39.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Houtarou?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:39.66,0:04:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're upset with how busy I am with the committee and Sewing Club.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:43.56,0:04:44.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm right, aren't I?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:44.94,0:04:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:46.17,0:04:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what, I am who I am.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:49.11,0:04:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not something people want me to be. {reflect with previous tl}
Dialogue: 5,0:04:51.55,0:04:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say you're colorless if I'm actually mocking you.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:57.65,0:05:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to be liked by you.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:01.60,0:05:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got a point there!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:03.13,0:05:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Houtarou.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:04.65,0:05:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you do on your midterms?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:06.23,0:05:07.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got an average grade in every subject.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:07.62,0:05:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect any less from you, Mr. Gray.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:11.01,0:05:12.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See that?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:12.16,0:05:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Chitanda estate.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:20.46,0:05:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:21.82,0:05:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it impressive?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:23.82,0:05:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:24.73,0:05:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're waiting for us.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:26.39,0:05:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:27.35,0:05:28.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:29.18,0:05:32.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it feel like a servant will come greet us?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:38.95,0:05:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:39.70,0:05:41.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been waiting.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:43.95,0:05:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Coming right in.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:45.92,0:05:47.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please follow me.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:02.35,0:06:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat wherever you'd like.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:06.38,0:06:07.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Took you long enough.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:08.17,0:06:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not late.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:12.56,0:06:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen someone look so out of place at the end of a table.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:17.06,0:06:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get this meeting underway.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:20.69,0:06:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:21.67,0:06:22.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:22.18,0:06:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aight.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:23.19,0:06:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today, I thought we could look over the events within the Classic Literature Club 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:28.83,0:06:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we come to a conclusion, I'd like to use it as part of this year's anthology.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:34.00,0:06:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, we'll distribute the documents and our reports.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:36.70,0:06:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll then have a question and answer session,
Dialogue: 5,0:06:38.88,0:06:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,followed by each of our hypotheses.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:40.87,0:06:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And to wrap it all up, we will analyze our hypotheses.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:44.46,0:06:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? She actually seems like a great host.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:47.05,0:06:49.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, would the first presenter...
Dialogue: 5,0:06:49.10,0:06:49.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:51.18,0:06:53.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who should present first?!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:53.80,0:06:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:54.58,0:06:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter who.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:56.39,0:06:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should start things off.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:57.89,0:06:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, you're right.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:59.49,0:07:01.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go clockwise starting from me.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:03.06,0:07:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I researched about Hyouka itself.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:06.19,0:07:10.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the preface mentions what happened 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:10.41,0:07:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I summarized the facts, which you can see in the second page.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:13.87,0:07:21.08,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(773,390)\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\t(1690,2107,\fs65)\move(477,40,458,33,1690,2107)}1.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35\t(1690,2107,\fs49)}The "upperclassman" left (from where?)
Dialogue: 1,0:07:13.87,0:07:15.95,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(773,390)\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(722,130)}2.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35}The "upperclassman" became a hero 45 years ago, and became a legend 44 years ago
Dialogue: 1,0:07:13.87,0:07:15.95,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(773,390)\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(608,275)}3.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35}The "upperclassman" was a "quiet fighter" and a "gentle hero."
Dialogue: 1,0:07:13.87,0:07:15.95,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(773,390)\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(564,358)}4.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35}The "upperclassman" gave birth to the name "Hyouka."
Dialogue: 1,0:07:13.87,0:07:15.95,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(773,390)\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(570,451)}5.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35}Conflict and sacrifice (sacrifice = the "upperclassman"?)
Dialogue: 5,0:07:15.04,0:07:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{mazu ichi}First, the "upperclassman" is my uncle, Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:20.68,0:07:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He dropped out of Kamiyama High,
Dialogue: 5,0:07:23.80,0:07:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{saishuu}and received no further education.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:26.21,0:07:30.05,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(773,726)\fs65\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\t(2947,3823,\fscx80\fscy80)\move(475,258,534,223,2947,3823)}2.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs45}The "upperclassman" became a hero 45 years\N\h\h\hago, and became a legend 44 years ago
Dialogue: 5,0:07:26.87,0:07:34.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second, I believe this means that the story would have gone through many changes.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.55,0:07:41.81,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(477,40)}1.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35}The "upperclassman" left (from where?)
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.55,0:07:41.81,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(722,130)}2.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35}The "upperclassman" became a hero 45 years ago, and became a legend 44 years ago
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.55,0:07:41.81,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(608,275)}3.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35}The "upperclassman" was a "quiet fighter" and a "gentle hero."
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.55,0:07:41.81,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(564,358)}4.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35}The "upperclassman" gave birth to the name "Hyouka."
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.55,0:07:41.81,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(570,451)}5.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35}Conflict and sacrifice (sacrifice = the "upperclassman"?)
Dialogue: 5,0:07:35.55,0:07:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{san to go}Three and five go hand in hand.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:38.10,0:07:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The quiet and gentle upperclassman became a fighter, then a hero.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:42.96,0:07:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{saigo wa}And in the end, he was sacrificed.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:46.69,0:07:50.03,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,144)\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(635,224)}4.\h\h\h\h\h{\fs35}The "upperclassman" gave birth to the name "Hyouka."
Dialogue: 5,0:07:47.37,0:07:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Four is quite intriguing, but let's not discuss it at this time.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:51.40,0:07:53.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all for my report.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:53.38,0:07:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any questions?
Dialogue: 1,0:07:55.62,0:07:59.75,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs55\c&H100F0F&\blur0.8\fnCallani\pos(523,108)\frx8\fry6\frz15.198}Heroic Tale
Dialogue: 5,0:07:55.62,0:08:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you skip over the "It was not a heroic tale in any way" part?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:00.76,0:08:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That part represents the writer's state of mind.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:03.31,0:08:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it means that it wasn't as glorified as it sounds, but that it was actually a struggle.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:08.40,0:08:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:09.90,0:08:12.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to present my hypothesis.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:12.59,0:08:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{oji wa}My uncle might have had a conflict with someone, so he decided to drop out.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:17.43,0:08:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've also looked into another element that hasn't been mentioned.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:22.61,0:08:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This part. "It's been a year since."
Dialogue: 5,0:08:25.35,0:08:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle dropped out in the season of Kanya Fest.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:29.20,0:08:35.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're getting a bit off topic, but a friend from another high school told me there was trouble in their cultural festival.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:35.09,0:08:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, cultural festival saboteurs, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:36.78,0:08:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The students were extorted and in the end, lose all their earnings!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:39.19,0:08:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that delinquents have always been around.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:43.88,0:08:48.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, Kanya Fest was their target that year.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:48.93,0:08:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So maybe my uncle resisted with violence and became a hero.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:54.63,0:09:00.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The juniors who mourned his loss must have left this behind.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:01.85,0:09:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hypothesis rejected.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:03.10,0:09:04.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, rejected.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:04.63,0:09:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:05.99,0:09:07.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please tell me why!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:07.56,0:09:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, do you remember what I suggested when we were talking about anthologies?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:13.88,0:09:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 5,0:09:15.55,0:09:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Food stalls?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:16.49,0:09:17.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:17.73,0:09:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you said that they've always been prohibited.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:21.74,0:09:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If there's no chance of making money, cultural festival saboteurs wouldn't show up.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:25.95,0:09:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think all saboteurs are after money.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:29.99,0:09:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pathetic, Houtarou.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:32.17,0:09:35.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Then let's hear your idea, Mr. Big Shot.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:35.94,0:09:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Believe it or not, cultural festival\Nsaboteurs didn't exist 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:41.57,0:09:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:42.66,0:09:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does anything about the '60s ring a bell?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:47.74,0:09:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokyo, the Diet Building, placards, demonstrations.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:52.44,0:09:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Satoshi?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:55.32,0:09:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Student protests.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:56.86,0:10:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sort of school violence that Chitanda is describing was rarely seen in the '60s.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:05.21,0:10:10.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was an era where people picked fights against the government instead of teachers and schools.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:10.77,0:10:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't act as if you've seen it first hand.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:13.07,0:10:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, I'm researching that time period.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:16.11,0:10:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's right. I didn't take history into account.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:19.72,0:10:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Chii!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:21.49,0:10:23.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you apologizing?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:23.62,0:10:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your hypothesis doesn't work according to my research.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:27.58,0:10:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I was next, I didn't know if I should've interrupted you.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:31.81,0:10:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, Ibara.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:33.10,0:10:34.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You made me listen to all that for nothing.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:34.73,0:10:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll put my speculation aside for now. Please let us hear yours.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:40.67,0:10:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all right with everyone else?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:42.25,0:10:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:43.87,0:10:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My legs are numb.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:47.31,0:10:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously though, this is a huge mansion.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:49.16,0:10:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a pond in your garden?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:51.60,0:10:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we do.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:53.04,0:10:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I would love to see it.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:55.74,0:10:57.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too!
Dialogue: 5,0:10:57.05,0:10:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's continue this in another place then.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:00.00,0:11:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our porch is very cozy!
Dialogue: 5,0:11:02.85,0:11:05.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A pond, huh?
Dialogue: 1,0:11:05.93,0:11:07.72,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,500)\blur2\bord0.8\an4\3c&H141514&\fnCicle Semi\fs76\b1\3c&H34445F&\c&H141514&\pos(541,363)}Boushu
Dialogue: 1,0:11:05.93,0:11:07.72,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,500)\blur0.8\an4\3c&H141514&\fnCicle Semi\fs76\b1\c&H141514&\pos(541,363)}Boushu
Dialogue: 1,0:11:05.93,0:11:08.89,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\bord0.4\an4\3c&H141514&\fnCicle Semi\fs36\3c&H34445F&\c&H141514&\pos(327,514)}The time to seed for crops
Dialogue: 1,0:11:05.93,0:11:08.89,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.8\an4\c&H141514&\fs36\fnCicle Semi\pos(327,514)}The time to seed for crops
Dialogue: 1,0:11:07.37,0:11:08.89,Show Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)\blur2\bord0.8\an4\3c&H141514&\fs76\b1\3c&H34445F&\c&H141514&\pos(521,366)}Hyouka
Dialogue: 1,0:11:07.37,0:11:08.89,Show Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(500,0)\blur2\bord0.8\an4\3c&H141514&\fs76\b1\3c&H34445F&\c&H141514&\pos(521,366)}Hyouka
Dialogue: 5,0:11:18.96,0:11:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a scan of this book I found in the library, {\i1}Unity & Triumph Vol. 1.{\i0}
Dialogue: 5,0:11:24.28,0:11:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't find any other volumes.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:26.45,0:11:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{hakkou}It was published 44 years ago, just like Chii's document.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:29.41,0:11:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Our relentless activism," huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:32.59,0:11:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds just like what I'd expect from this era.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:34.82,0:11:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, here I go.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:35.96,0:11:37.00,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(69,95)\fs225\c&H100F0F&\blur0.9\fnCartoonDemiBold\pos(692,139)}We
Dialogue: 5,0:11:35.99,0:11:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assume that "we" means "students,"
Dialogue: 1,0:11:37.00,0:11:38.13,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs85\c&H100F0F&\blur0.9\fnCartoonDemiBold\pos(925,41)}We
Dialogue: 5,0:11:38.13,0:11:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while "reflexive forces" and \N"authoritarians" means teachers.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:38.21,0:11:40.26,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,95)\fs99\blur0.9\fnCartoonDemiBold\c&H0C1213&\pos(646,44)}Reac{\c&H3048A6&}tion{\c&H0B1113&}ary Forces
Dialogue: 1,0:11:38.21,0:11:40.26,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,95)\fs99\blur0.9\fnCartoonDemiBold\c&H0C1213&\pos(639,109)}Authorita{\c&H3048A6&}rian{\c&H0C1213&}s
Dialogue: 1,0:11:42.51,0:11:44.76,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs99\blur0.9\fnCartoonDemiBold\c&H0C1213&\frx38\fry6\pos(646,64)}June
Dialogue: 5,0:11:42.51,0:11:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During the previous June, there was a huge clash between the students,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:45.00,0:11:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the Classic Literature Club's president, Sekitani Jun, led the movement.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:49.16,0:11:53.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They then executed this "activism," causing trouble with the teachers.
Dialogue: 1,0:11:49.22,0:11:51.39,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(72,180)\fs99\blur0.9\fnCartoonDemiBold\c&H0C1213&\pos(642,132)}Act{\c&H3048AC&}ivis{\c&H0C1213&}m
Dialogue: 5,0:11:54.69,0:11:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. So it's clash, not conflict?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:58.56,0:12:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Unity & Triumph book looks pretty fishy.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:02.23,0:12:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fishy? How?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:03.92,0:12:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not doubting its authenticity.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:06.61,0:12:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It just sounds like someone who admired student protests wrote it.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:10.75,0:12:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what about it?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:12.84,0:12:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing, I was just talking to myself.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:14.64,0:12:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:15.67,0:12:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Any other questions?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:19.63,0:12:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll move on to my hypothesis, then.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:21.42,0:12:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But before that, I'll disprove Chii's hypothesis.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:23.72,0:12:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to Unity & Triumph, the incident occurred in June.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:28.10,0:12:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did something that led to expulsion.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:30.93,0:12:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can only think of violence.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:32.86,0:12:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This means those who followed Sekitani Jun...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:39.11,0:12:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bam! They attacked the teachers.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:40.99,0:12:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if they actually hit them,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:43.49,0:12:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but something happened 45 years ago that endangered a students' individuality,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:47.82,0:12:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they retaliated.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:50.42,0:12:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My uncle was their leader?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:53.97,0:12:56.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see where you're getting at, but...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:56.50,0:12:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:58.04,0:13:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that a student used violence against the teachers' suppression.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:04.48,0:13:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:05.72,0:13:08.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your speculation is too abstract.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:08.18,0:13:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's not like you can go more in-depth anyway.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:10.85,0:13:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true I didn't get into the specifics,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:14.09,0:13:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but were there any contradictions?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:15.16,0:13:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:15.89,0:13:18.77,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,139)\fs70\b1\blur0.9\fnDisney Simple\pos(194,154)\c&H3D3F3F&}Hyouka
Dialogue: 1,0:13:15.89,0:13:19.94,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,141)\fs70\b1\blur0.9\fnDisney Simple\c&H3D3F3F&\pos(1102,258)}Unity\Nand\NRejoice
Dialogue: 5,0:13:16.34,0:13:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming both Hyouka and Unity & Triumph are true,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:18.80,0:13:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{jiken}then the incident occurred in June, and he was expelled on the month of the cultural festival, October.
Dialogue: 1,0:13:18.90,0:13:23.24,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(315,229)\fs50\b1\blur0.9\fnDisney Simple\c&H3D3F3F&\pos(350,354)}Incident\N{\fs66}June
Dialogue: 1,0:13:20.07,0:13:23.24,Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(315,229)\fs50\b1\blur0.9\fnDisney Simple\c&H3D3F3F&\pos(941,356)}Expelled\N{\fs66}October
Dialogue: 5,0:13:22.66,0:13:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's a punitive action for violence, then he should've been expelled right after the incident.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:26.71,0:13:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:27.53,0:13:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This four-month gap bothers me as well.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:31.06,0:13:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They saying "it's been a year" by the time of the cultural festival,
Dialogue: 5,0:13:33.91,0:13:35.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so the expulsion was probably in October.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:36.97,0:13:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're all so picky.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:39.37,0:13:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you're on the right direction.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:41.70,0:13:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:43.04,0:13:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So is that the end of my turn?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:46.10,0:13:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Thank you.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:47.79,0:13:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next up...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:49.01,0:13:51.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My bad. I'm pretty hungry.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:52.12,0:13:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good grief. Haven't you eaten enough snacks already?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:54.60,0:13:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:56.39,0:13:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can make some rice balls if you'd like.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:58.48,0:14:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we all take a break?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:15.11,0:14:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything I can do to help, Chii?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:18.35,0:14:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine here.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:19.96,0:14:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:21.00,0:14:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:25.01,0:14:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hand-made!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:26.95,0:14:28.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You ecstatic little bastard.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:29.30,0:14:30.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuku, what's this?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:30.78,0:14:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Mayaka!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:32.77,0:14:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My research disproves part of your hypothesis.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:36.89,0:14:38.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot to mention it.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:38.29,0:14:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:42.38,0:14:44.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this Kami High's Monthly Report?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:44.36,0:14:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. Toukaidou mentioned that they were nearing 500 issues.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:48.29,0:14:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:49.53,0:14:54.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My research was on archives of the Wall Newspaper Club's Monthly Report.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:54.74,0:14:59.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This was all I could find from 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:59.46,0:15:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The summary is on the next page.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:01.71,0:15:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first and the last entries are what we already have.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:04.57,0:15:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Violence wasn't used in the incident,
Dialogue: 5,0:15:06.88,0:15:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so Mayaka's hypothesis needs some reworking.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:08.97,0:15:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, if "the entire school" here is what they mean by "we,"
Dialogue: 5,0:15:13.26,0:15:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then all the students must have been involved in the incident.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:16.35,0:15:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, someone was there to organize the entire school.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:20.64,0:15:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:24.05,0:15:25.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Chii.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:25.60,0:15:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mention it.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:27.01,0:15:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are plum, kelp, and leaf mustard fillings.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:29.38,0:15:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please try them.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:32.32,0:15:34.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:35.61,0:15:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:36.41,0:15:37.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:42.42,0:15:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's good!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:43.59,0:15:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's delicious!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:45.00,0:15:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is the rice made in your farm?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:47.96,0:15:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:49.86,0:15:51.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can ask your questions now.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:51.75,0:15:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure this legendary protest was the cause of Sekitani Jun's expulsion?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:56.70,0:15:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think this scan is conclusive.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:58.70,0:15:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:59.71,0:16:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't prove it.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:00.64,0:16:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Who knows?"
Dialogue: 5,0:16:02.40,0:16:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't use this for research, then.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:04.33,0:16:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:05.89,0:16:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we have indirect evidence.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:08.85,0:16:10.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sekitani Jun's incident,
Dialogue: 5,0:16:10.70,0:16:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the legendary protest are different.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:12.93,0:16:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means there should be a line that says "this is the legendary one" instead.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:16.78,0:16:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That's what I wanted to say!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:19.49,0:16:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really get me, Mayaka.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:22.21,0:16:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hear your hypothesis, then.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:25.31,0:16:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hypothesis, huh?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:26.39,0:16:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:27.62,0:16:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda, I'm sorry, but I can't make a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:30.96,0:16:34.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can barely correct Ibara's speculation with what I have.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:34.72,0:16:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention,
Dialogue: 5,0:16:36.20,0:16:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a database can't come to a conclusion.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:38.82,0:16:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew he'd say that.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:41.81,0:16:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:44.24,0:16:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What will I do with this?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:45.45,0:16:47.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay then, Oreki. If you'd please.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:52.57,0:16:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou, is this...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:54.65,0:16:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kamiyama High's 50 Years of Journey?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:57.53,0:17:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering if we could find something in the official records.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:01.95,0:17:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now that I look at it again, there's nothing of significance here.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:06.75,0:17:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a hypothesis either.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:08.30,0:17:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What will I do now?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:09.63,0:17:11.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Houtarou?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:12.37,0:17:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, have you already forgotten the process?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:15.78,0:17:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, you present your information.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:19.65,0:17:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this really even necessary?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:23.96,0:17:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Houtarou?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:26.69,0:17:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:29.06,0:17:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:32.15,0:17:33.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:33.89,0:17:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need a way out of this.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:39.87,0:17:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:41.79,0:17:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot I was drying some Shiitake mushrooms.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:45.14,0:17:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to take them inside.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:46.71,0:17:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need any help?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:48.17,0:17:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can handle it.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:50.25,0:17:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:51.40,0:17:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:51.67,0:17:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but can I use your bathroom?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:55.27,0:17:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exit this room, then go straight.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:59.50,0:18:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you, nervous?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:02.56,0:18:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go straight... Go straight.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:10.80,0:18:12.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm lost.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:27.06,0:18:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She did this much research?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:30.37,0:18:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I should use my head.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:36.35,0:18:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,45 years ago, something happened to Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:41.33,0:18:42.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are four documents.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:43.50,0:18:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do they have in common?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:47.35,0:18:48.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:51.48,0:18:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Student protest.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:53.02,0:18:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Violence.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:54.69,0:18:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gap in expulsion.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:58.05,0:19:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,45 years ago, Sekitani Jun was...
Dialogue: 5,0:19:03.89,0:19:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Took you long enough.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:05.45,0:19:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, {\i1}sorry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:07.43,0:19:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn to present, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:10.01,0:19:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I didn't have a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:12.33,0:19:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's end my turn,
Dialogue: 5,0:19:14.39,0:19:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and come to the conclusion.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:16.35,0:19:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came up with a solution, didn't you?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:18.45,0:19:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sort of. I think it'll explain most of the mysteries.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:22.18,0:19:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You figured something out, Oreki?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:24.10,0:19:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Chitanda. Relax!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:26.76,0:19:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hear what he's got.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:28.92,0:19:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't disappoint us.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:31.44,0:19:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. Let's take it from the top.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:35.19,0:19:37.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, {\i1}when.{\i0}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:37.03,0:19:38.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was 45 years ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:38.50,0:19:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The problem is what time of the year.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:40.45,0:19:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we trust both Hyouka and Unity & Triumph,
Dialogue: 5,0:19:44.10,0:19:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then the incident happened in June, and he left in October.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:48.20,0:19:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, {\i1}where.{\i0}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:50.08,0:19:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was in Kamiyama High School.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:52.15,0:19:52.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, {\i1}who.{\i0}
Dialogue: 5,0:19:53.65,0:19:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From Unity & Triumph, Sekitani Jun is the center of everything.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:59.34,0:20:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to Kami High Monthly Report,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:01.13,0:20:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the entire school was involved with the incident as well.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:04.34,0:20:06.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, {\i1}why.{\i0}
Dialogue: 5,0:20:06.06,0:20:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Students would only protest against a certain type of person.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:08.75,0:20:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, the teachers.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:10.44,0:20:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using Ibara's words,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:12.67,0:20:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the reason they stood up was because their independence was lost.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:15.78,0:20:18.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the cause of the incident is...
Dialogue: 5,0:20:20.47,0:20:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the cultural festival.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:22.61,0:20:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it written somewhere that the cultural festival was responsible for the incident?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:26.91,0:20:28.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, but judging from what happened,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:28.45,0:20:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think there was a debate between the teachers and students on June,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:32.65,0:20:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the cultural festival was held on October.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:36.78,0:20:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By debate, you mean this "Cultural Festival Discussion Meeting?"
Dialogue: 5,0:20:41.09,0:20:42.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:42.22,0:20:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a closer look.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:45.55,0:20:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are circle and square marks on top of each line.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:49.20,0:20:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:49.88,0:20:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Squares are yearly events,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:52.31,0:20:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{maru ga}and circles are events unique to that year!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:55.19,0:20:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I checked other years too. That's seems to be the case.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:59.37,0:21:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why was the only Cultural Festival \NDiscussion Meeting held 45 years ago?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:03.68,0:21:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There must have been strong demands from students.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:06.70,0:21:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hint can be found in Hyouka.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:09.46,0:21:10.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right here.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:10.80,0:21:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"In a single year, he turned from a hero into a legend.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:14.14,0:21:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"the cultural festival will be held once again for five days of glory."
Dialogue: 5,0:21:18.09,0:21:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The key here isn't "held once again,"
Dialogue: 5,0:21:19.94,0:21:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but "five days" part.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:22.50,0:21:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:23.76,0:21:28.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Five days" is the achievement of the hero, Sekitani Jun.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:28.14,0:21:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just my guess, but the principal's "Declaration of Focus on Education" is related.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:33.22,0:21:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The principal might have tried to shorten the five days of cultural festival.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:38.52,0:21:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why the entire school was engulfed in rage.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:43.12,0:21:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the cause of the incident, {\i1}why.{\i0}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:46.22,0:21:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As well as the actual action, {\i1}how.{\i0}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:49.70,0:21:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Under Classic Literature Club president, Sekitani Jun's
Dialogue: 5,0:21:51.95,0:21:53.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,heroic guidance,
Dialogue: 5,0:21:53.60,0:21:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{kakan}relentless activism was held.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:56.41,0:21:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which leads to the final item, what.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:58.97,0:22:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The student's didn't use violence.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:01.59,0:22:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They must have boycotted at most.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:04.38,0:22:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The staff had no choice but to negotiate with the students,
Dialogue: 5,0:22:07.51,0:22:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and refrained from shortening the cultural festival.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:10.01,0:22:14.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the hero, Sekitani Jun was expelled in exchange.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:14.39,0:22:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As for why there's a gap in the incident and expulsion...
Dialogue: 5,0:22:17.61,0:22:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the conflict would only get more out of hand if Sekitani Jun was expelled back then.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:21.16,0:22:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it happened after the craze, after the cultural festival.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:26.80,0:22:28.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all for my conclusion.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:36.52,0:22:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something like that happened to my uncle...
Dialogue: 5,0:22:43.38,0:22:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed, Oreki.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:47.17,0:22:50.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was pretty impressive, Houtarou.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:50.35,0:22:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It all checks out.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:51.60,0:22:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki did it again! I can't believe it!
Dialogue: 5,0:22:55.35,0:22:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just lucky.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:57.60,0:22:59.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there any questions?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:59.85,0:23:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:01.47,0:23:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate to admit it, but I think he's right.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:04.51,0:23:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's base our anthology this year on Oreki's conclusion.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:10.17,0:23:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll inform you of the details in a few days.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:12.86,0:23:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This meeting is adjourned.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:14.34,0:23:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work, everyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:17.67,0:23:20.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:20.65,0:23:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it on my own.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:22.90,0:23:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's all thanks to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:25.85,0:23:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for lending me an umbrella.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:28.23,0:23:29.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See you.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:49.76,0:23:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he's right, why did I...
Dialogue: 5,0:23:53.41,0:23:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,cry back then?
